  "description": [
    "The Republican Journal Belfast Thursday Aug 7 1919 PUBLISHED EVERY THURSDAY BY The Republican journal Pub Co A I BROWN Editor ADVERTISING T ERMS For one square one inch length in column 70 cents for one week and 37 cuts for each subsequent insertion SUBSCRIPTION Terms In advance 200 a year 5100 for six months 50 cents for three months KOREA Korea the country which is being per secuted b Japan is about two and one half times the size of Maine and is consid erably more than half as large as Japan Its population is not definitely known but a census of Us adult taxpayers was taken in 1901 which enumerated 5608351 people Hence it is safe to place the en tire number of inhabitants as being be tween 20 and 30 millions or about one j third the population of Japan Korea is a peninsula about 500 miles long extend j mg southward from Manchuria and is be tween the sea of Japan on the east and for the most part by the Yellow sea on the west The southern part of Japan is separated from the southern part of Korea by the strait of Korea which is"
